

npx create-next-app@latest my-app --yes
cd my-app
npm run dev

Create and implement a simple next js app like the above.
The app is supposed to be a word list memorization helper called "Walden's Word Trainer"

It should let you make accounts with Better Auth, and when you log in you can create a word list. Use prisma and sqlite for the ORM. To keep it simple, word lists are public for all users.
Then you can study a word list. It should give you a text box to type in a word. Then when you hit enter it should submit the word. If its in the list that's a success, otherwise failure.
When you are done hit done button, and it will show you in two sections, 1. the words you didn't remember. And 2. The words you got incorrect.


